 Port Elizabeth - Police in Bethesldorp, Port Elizabeth, are seeking the community’s assistance in tracing the next of kin of an unidentified man found dead on Sunday, 20 October. According to police information, the body was found at about 06:00 in an open field in Lee Samuels Street in Ext 36 in Bethelsdorp. "The male approximately 35-year-old was badly burnt," said police spokesperson, Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana. "At this stage, the circumstances surrounding the incident is not known and police are investigating a case of murder. "Anyone who can assist in tracing or identifying the body is asked to contact D/Sgt TE Nobebe at SAPS Bethelsdorp on 041 404 3054." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 